== Fact of the Day ==

[[Image:Reverse necrophilia1.jpg|thumb|Reverse Necrophilia]]

In [[New Hampshire]] common-law [[marriage]] can still only be contracted posthumously. [[Brain dead]] patients are not accepted as spouses under New Hampshire's [[right-to-life]] legislation, whereas potential partners with an [[Retarded|IQ under 50]] are legally defined as non-sentient and are therefore [[Scientology|fair game]] in the "Go to the mountain" state.


